--> START SERVER & CLIENTS:
    Open the terminal and make the source files. run the exec file with right arguments (<port> <serverPassword>). port is a number that other clients can connect with the server from it. the serverPassword is the a password from the choose of the user.
    you can open new terminal (without closing the old one). run the commond "nc 127.0.0.1 <port>" nc command create new connection with localhost (127.0.0.1) in the port (<port> is the same as the server). and congratulations, now you are connected with the server and you can interact with other clients.
--> AUTHENTICATION:
    After connecting with the server, a message will be shown on your prompt at your terminal says that you connected with the server and now you have to enter the server password and you nickname and username as follows:
    pass <serverPassword>
    nick <nickname>
    user <username>

 Available Commands

Below is a list of supported commands for interacting with the IRC server. Replace #channel, user, or other placeholders with the actual channel name, username, or relevant values.

<JOIN>
<Join a specified channel.
Syntax: JOIN #channel
Example: JOIN #sabona
Description: Connects you to the specified channel, allowing you to participate in discussions.>

<PRIVMSG>
<Send and receive private messages to a channel or a specific client.
Syntax: PRIVMSG #channel|user "message"
Examples:
To a channel: PRIVMSG #sabona Hello, everyone!
To a user: PRIVMSG alice Hi, how are you?
Description: Sends a message to either a channel or an individual user.>

<KICK>
<Eject a client from a channel (requires operator privileges).
Syntax: KICK #channel user
Example: KICK #sabona bob
Description: Removes the specified user from the channel.>

<INVITE>
<Invite a client to a channel.
Syntax: INVITE user #channel
Example: INVITE alice #sabona
Description: Sends an invitation to the specified user to join the channel.>

<TOPIC>
<View or change the channel's topic.
Syntax:
To view: TOPIC #channel
To change: TOPIC #channel NEW_TOPIC
Examples:
View topic: TOPIC #sabona
Change topic: TOPIC #sabona Welcome to our community!
Description: Displays the current topic or updates it to a new one (may require operator privileges to change).>

<MODE>
<Change the channel's mode to configure its settings.
Syntax: MODE #channel mode
Supported Modes:
i: Set/remove Invite-only channel.
t: Set/remove restrictions on the TOPIC command to channel operators only.
k: Set/remove the channel key (password).
o: Give/take channel operator privileges.
l: Set/remove the user limit for the channel.
Examples:
Set invite-only: MODE #sabona +i
Remove password: MODE #sabona -k
Grant operator status: MODE #sabona +o alice
Description: Modifies channel settings to control access, permissions, or behavior (requires operator privileges).>